<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
    Foreground for the adaptive launcher icon: a single-stroke
    geometric "S" rendered on the saffron background.

    The path is the SPINE of the letter (the centerline a pen would
    trace), drawn as three cubic Béziers:

      M 80,36                                      [top-right tip]
      C 80,24 28,24 28,36     [top arc → apex (54,27)]
      C 28,54 80,54 80,72     [middle wave → exact center (54,54)]
      C 80,84 28,84 28,72     [bottom arc → dip (54,81)]

    Symmetric on x=54. The three control-point pairs are placed so the
    cubic midpoints land at (54,27), (54,54) and (54,81) respectively —
    that's the visual rhythm a sophisticated S needs: equal upper
    counter, exact-center wave, equal lower counter.

    Rendered as a STROKED path (no fill) with width 11 + round caps and
    joins so the terminals at (80,36) and (28,72) are soft semicircles
    rather than blunt square ends.

    With stroke=11, the visible glyph sits within the 66 dp adaptive-icon
    safe zone (centre 54, radius 33 → y range 21..87) — even the most
    aggressive circular launcher mask won't crop the S.
-->
<vector xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:width="108dp"
    android:height="108dp"
    android:viewportWidth="108"
    android:viewportHeight="108">
    <path
        android:strokeColor="#FFFFFF"
        android:strokeWidth="11"
        android:strokeLineCap="round"
        android:strokeLineJoin="round"
        android:fillColor="#00FFFFFF"
        android:pathData="M80,36 C80,24 28,24 28,36 C28,54 80,54 80,72 C80,84 28,84 28,72" />
</vector>
